kernel = np.ones((3,3),np.uint8)
opening = cv2.morphologyEx(th,cv2.MORPH_OPEN,kernel, iterations = 2)

# sure background area
sure_bg = cv2.dilate(opening,kernel,iterations=3)

# Finding sure foreground area
dist_transform = cv2.distanceTransform(opening,cv2.DIST_L2,5)
ret, sure_fg = cv2.threshold(dist_transform,0.05*dist_transform.max(),255,0)

# Finding unknown region
sure_fg = np.uint8(sure_fg)
unknown = cv2.subtract(sure_bg,sure_fg)

# Marker labelling
ret, markers = cv2.connectedComponents(sure_fg)

# Add one to all labels so that sure background is not 0, but 1
markers = markers+1

# Now, mark the region of unknown with zero
markers[unknown==255] = 0

markers = cv2.watershed(scenery1,markers)
scenery1[markers == -1] = [255,0,0]

In [11]:
def watershed1(original,count):
    global res_img
    img = cv2.cvtColor(original, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
    ret,th = cv2.threshold(img,0,255,cv2.THRESH_BINARY+cv2.THRESH_OTSU)
    
    # noise removal
    kernel = np.ones((3,3),np.uint8)
    opening = cv2.morphologyEx(th,cv2.MORPH_OPEN,kernel, iterations = 2)
    
    # sure background area
    sure_bg = cv2.dilate(opening,kernel,iterations=3)
    
    # Finding sure foreground area
    dist_transform = cv2.distanceTransform(opening,cv2.DIST_L2,5)
    ret, sure_fg = cv2.threshold(dist_transform,0.05*dist_transform.max(),255,0)
    
    # Finding unknown region
    sure_fg = np.uint8(sure_fg)
    unknown = cv2.subtract(sure_bg,sure_fg)
    
    # Marker labelling
    ret, markers = cv2.connectedComponents(sure_fg)
    
    # Add one to all labels so that sure background is not 0, but 1
    markers = markers+1
    
    # Now, mark the region of unknown with zero
    markers[unknown==255] = 0
    markers = cv2.watershed(original,markers)
    original[markers == -1] = [255,0,0]
    
  #  plt.subplot(4,1,count),plt.imshow(original)

our_thread1 = threading.Thread( target=watershed1, args=(scenery1[:255,:,:],1))
our_thread2 = threading.Thread( target=watershed1, args=(scenery1[256:511,:,:],2))
our_thread3 = threading.Thread( target=watershed1, args=(scenery1[512:767,:,:],3))
our_thread4 = threading.Thread( target=watershed1, args=(scenery1[768:,:,:],4))

now = time.time()
our_thread1.start()
our_thread2.start()
our_thread3.start()
our_thread4.start()
our_thread1.join()
our_thread2.join()
our_thread3.join()
our_thread4.join()
end = time.time()
print (end-now)

In [17]:
def mse(imageA, imageB):
    err = np.sum((imageA.astype("float") - imageB.astype("float")) ** 2)
    err /= float(imageA.shape[0] * imageA.shape[1])
    return err
